the 2009 honduras earthquake occurred on may 28 at 02:24:45 am local time with a moment magnitude of 7.3 and a maximum mercalli intensity of vii (very strong). the epicenter was located in the caribbean sea, 64 kilometres (40 mi) northeast of the island of roat√°n, 19 miles northeast of port royal, isla de bahias, 15 miles northwest of isla barbaretta, and 130 kilometres (81 mi) north-northeast of la ceiba. three aftershocks followed the earthquake within magnitude 4 range.